---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Personal Loan for Low CIBIL Score (550-700) | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Personal Loan for Low CIBIL Score</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Personal Loan for Low CIBIL Score</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Struggling with a low CIBIL score? Get personal loans approved even with scores between 550 and 700. Our partner lenders specialize in offering fair-rate loans to applicants with imperfect credit histories. Apply now and get funded within 48 hours.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹25K - ₹10L</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
          <span>CIBIL Score: 550+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 16% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>Can You Get a Personal Loan with a Low CIBIL Score?</h2>
          <p>Yes, it is possible to get a personal loan even with a CIBIL score between 550 and 700. While traditional banks prefer applicants with scores above 750, several NBFCs and fintech lenders on the TrueCred platform specialize in serving borrowers with lower credit scores. These lenders evaluate your overall financial profile — including income stability, employment history, and banking behaviour — rather than relying solely on the credit score.</p>
          <p>Loans for low CIBIL scores typically come with higher interest rates (16% to 30% p.a.) and lower loan amounts (₹25,000 to ₹10,00,000) compared to standard personal loans. However, they provide a crucial lifeline for emergencies and also offer an opportunity to rebuild your credit score through timely repayments. At TrueCred, we match you with lenders most likely to approve your application based on your unique profile.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">550+</span>
              <span class="info-label">Min CIBIL Score</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹10 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">48 Hrs</span>
              <span class="info-label">Disbursal Time</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Personal Loan Rates for Low CIBIL Score — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Bajaj Finserv</td>
                <td>16.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Tata Capital</td>
                <td>17.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.50%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Fullerton India</td>
                <td>18.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.00%</td>
                <td>4 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Muthoot Finance</td>
                <td>16.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>CASHe</td>
                <td>21.00% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 3.50%</td>
                <td>3 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 550 or above (some lenders accept scores from 500)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum monthly income of ₹12,000 from a verifiable source</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Age between 21 and 55 years at the time of application</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> No active loan default or written-off account in the last 6 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> At least 1 year of work experience in current employment</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Stable bank account with regular transactions for the past 6 months</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Get a Loan with Low CIBIL Score</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Know Your Score</h4>
              <p>Check your free CIBIL score on TrueCred and understand the factors pulling it down before applying.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Match with Lenders</h4>
              <p>Our algorithm matches you with NBFCs and fintech lenders who specialize in low-score applicants.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Apply with Documents</h4>
              <p>Submit your application along with income proof and bank statements for faster approval.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Get Approved & Improve</h4>
              <p>Receive funds within 48 hours. Make timely EMI payments to steadily improve your credit score.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Identity Proof — Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, or Voter ID</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Address Proof — Aadhaar Card, Utility Bill, or Rent Agreement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Income Proof — Latest 3 months salary slips or bank statements showing income</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Bank Statements — Last 6 months showing regular credits and debits</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Employment Proof — Company ID card, offer letter, or any employment verification</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Passport-size photographs (2 copies)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for Low CIBIL Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="25000">₹25,000</option>
                  <option value="50000">₹50,000</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="300000">₹3,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="700000">₹7,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about personal loans for low CIBIL scores.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the minimum CIBIL score needed to get a personal loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              While most banks require a score of 700+, several NBFCs and fintech lenders on TrueCred approve loans for scores as low as 550. Lenders like Bajaj Finserv, Fullerton India, and CASHe evaluate your overall profile beyond just the score. Having stable income, clean recent credit history, and no active defaults significantly improve your chances.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Will my interest rate decrease if my CIBIL score improves?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Your current loan's interest rate is typically fixed at disbursement. However, once your score improves to 700+, you can apply for a balance transfer to a lender offering lower rates. After 12-18 months of timely repayments, your score can improve by 50-100 points, making you eligible for much better rates on your next loan.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How can I improve my CIBIL score quickly?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Pay all EMIs and credit card bills on time, reduce credit card utilization below 30%, avoid multiple loan applications in a short period, check your CIBIL report for errors and dispute them, and maintain a healthy mix of secured and unsecured credit. With consistent effort, you can see improvement within 3-6 months.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I get a personal loan with a CIBIL score of 500?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Getting a personal loan with a score of 500 is challenging but not impossible. A few fintech lenders may approve small-ticket loans (₹25,000 to ₹1,00,000) at higher interest rates if you have stable income and no recent defaults. Alternatively, consider a secured loan against FD or gold as a stepping stone to rebuild credit.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Are there any special schemes for first-time borrowers with no CIBIL history?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, individuals with a thin credit file (little or no credit history) are different from those with low scores. Many lenders offer first-time borrower programs with moderate rates. TrueCred partners with lenders who use alternative data like banking transactions, education, and employment to assess such applicants. Loan amounts may start smaller but help build your credit profile.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Get a Personal Loan Despite Low CIBIL Score</h3>
          <p>Our partner lenders specialize in low-score approvals. Apply now with scores as low as 550.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
